[*] [b]Nexus Mods[/b]: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2183]Simple Hotkeys[/url]
[/list]
[h2][b]Hotkey Actions[/b][/h2]

All of the actions below show up automatically on the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i]'s [b]Hotkey Bindings[/b] page once this mod is enabled - there is nothing to configure here, just assign a key to whichever ones you want to use.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-Simple-Hotkeys/refs/heads/main/docs/images/hotkey_bindings.png[/img]
[list]
[*] [b]Rename Selected/Targeted Object[/b] - opens the vanilla rename popup for the selected (map) or targeted (piloting) object, if it's player-owned.
[*] [b]Follow Target[/b] - engages autopilot to the current target (which tracks a moving target, i.e. "follow"); pressed again on the same target, it disengages autopilot instead.
[*] [b]Eject Illegal Wares[/b] - drops all illegal cargo from the ship's hold and the player's own inventory, based on the local sector's police faction.
[*] [b]Print Combined Skill of Target[/b] - shows a notification with the combined skill of the current target's crew.
[*] [b]Zoom In (Flight Mode)[/b] - piloting only: steps the camera FOV through increasing zoom factors (1x -> 2x -> 4x -> 8x) on repeated presses; pressing again once at the highest factor resets straight back to the FOV that was active before zooming started.
[*] [b]Launch Satellite / Launch Advanced Satellite[/b] - launches a satellite or advanced satellite, if one is carried.
[*] [b]Launch Laser Tower Mk1 / Mk2[/b] - launches a laser tower of the chosen mark, if one is carried.
[*] [b]Launch Mine / Launch Tracker Mine / Launch Friend-or-Foe Mine[/b] - launches the chosen mine type, if one is carried.
[*] [b]Map: Launch ...[/b] - map-only counterpart of every launch action above (Satellite, Advanced Satellite, Laser Tower Mk1/Mk2, Mine, Tracker Mine, Friend-or-Foe Mine), plus [b]Map: Launch Resource Probe[/b] / [b]Map: Launch Navigation Beacon[/b] (no piloting counterpart - vanilla already has hotkeys for those from the ship you're piloting): launches onto the selected player-owned ship on the map instead of the ship you're piloting, if it's carrying one.
[*] [b]Toggle Right Info Panel[/b] - map only: toggles the map's right-side info panel for the current selection, mirroring the existing sidebar icon (there's no vanilla hotkey for either side's info panel, only mouse clicks).
[*] [b]Take Command of Ship (FPS Mode)[/b] - lets you take the pilot/flight-control seat of the ship you're walking in via hotkey, where appropriate "option" is shown on walking crosshair.
[/list]
Please note - you can disable any of these actions in the appropriate [b]Hotkey Requests[/b] section of the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i]'s menu, if you don't want to use them.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-Simple-Hotkeys/refs/heads/main/docs/images/hotkey_requests.png[/img]
[list]
[*] [b]Object List / Property Owned[/b] -  configurable hotkeys for every tab of the map's [b]Object List[/b] panel and every tab of the map's [b]Property Owned[/b] panel, read directly from the game itself so the list always matches what's actually available, including anything future game updates add.
[*] [b]Player Info[/b] - configurable hotkeys for every section of the [b]Player Info[/b] menu (Empire, Statistics, Inventory, Modifications, Spacesuit Upgrades, Global Orders, Account Management, Personnel Management, Messages, Transaction Log, Logbook, Contacts), read directly from the game itself so the list always matches what's actually available, including anything future game updates add.
[/list]
[h2][b]Configurable Hotkey Groups[/b][/h2]

Beyond the always-on actions above, this mod adds a few more [b]opt-in[/b] hotkey groups, configured from the Options menu rather than appearing automatically - since these can add a lot of individual hotkeys, they all default to disabled so they don't clutter your keybinding list unless you actually want them.

You'll find them on the same [b]Options > Hotkey Management[/b] page the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i] itself adds, right below its own Hotkey Bindings / Hotkey Requests / Debug Logging rows - no separate menu, no extra dependencies.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-Simple-Hotkeys/refs/heads/main/docs/images/configuration.png[/img]

[h2]Launch Hotkeys[/h2]

Two toggles that enable/disable the entire deployable-launch hotkey family (Launch Satellite, Launch Mine, etc., and their [b]Map:[/b] counterparts) listed above:
[list]
[*] [b]Enable Launch Hotkeys in Pilot Mode for Current Ship[/b]
[*] [b]Enable Launch Hotkeys in Map Mode for Selected Ship[/b]
[/list]
Both are enabled by default.

[h2]Object List / Property Owned / Player Info Hotkeys[/h2]

These three sections each list every tab of the map's [b]Object List[/b] panel, every tab of the map's [b]Property Owned[/b] panel, and every section of the [b]Player Info[/b] menu (Empire, Statistics, Inventory, Modifications, Spacesuit Upgrades, Global Orders, Account Management, Personnel Management, Messages, Transaction Log, Logbook, Contacts) - read directly from the game itself, so the list always matches what's actually available, including anything future game updates add.

Each tab/section gets its own dropdown, letting you pick exactly which ones get a hotkey and how:
[list]
[*] [b]Disabled[/b] (default) - no hotkey for this tab/section.
[*] [b]Pilot Mode Only[/b] - a hotkey that opens straight to this tab/section while you're piloting (no menu open).
[*] [b]Map Mode Only[/b] - a hotkey that switches straight to this tab/section while the map (or Player Info menu) is already open.
[*] [b]Pilot & Map (Unified Hotkey)[/b] - a single hotkey that works from either context: opens the relevant menu fresh if nothing's open, or switches live if it's already open.
[/list]
Changing any of these dropdowns takes effect immediately - no need to reopen Options or reload the game.

